turn-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2528973\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 14, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104jon1665702865162.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jon1665702865162.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jon1665702865162.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"jon1665702865162\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Using Uniface Authentication\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">\n</p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"jon1665702865162__context_w1211ab1b5b1_w1212ab1b5_w1213ab1\">\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"jon1665702865162__topic_d22568e1_d22569e1_d22570e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jon1665702865162__p_d22571e1_d22572e1_d22573e1\">To use Uniface’s authentication method:</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"jon1665702865162__li_d11042e1_d11043e1_d11044e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"jon1665702865162__p_d22574e1_d22575e1_d22576e1\">In the servlet specification, add the\n                  <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">AUTHORIZATION</span> parameter, for example,</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">&lt;servlet&gt; \n &lt;servlet-name&gt; \n wrd\n … …\n &lt;init-param&gt; \n &lt;param-name&gt;AUTHORIZATION&lt;/param-name&gt; \n &lt;param-value&gt;Realm&lt;/param-value&gt;\n &lt;/init-param&gt;\n&lt;/servlet&gt;</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\">If the Web server is Tomcat, the servlet specification is in\n                     <span class=\"ph filepath\">web.xml</span>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jon1665702865162__p_d22577e1_d22578e1_d22579e1\">With this setting, a logon box is displayed for\n                  each first access of a server page by a particular user. The user name and\n                  password are available for the duration of the whole session. You can use\n                     <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$user</span>and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$password</span>to access them.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jon1665702865162__p_d22580e1_d22581e1_d22582e1\">To validate the user name and password, you need\n                  to add ProcScript in the server page, or in the startup shell of the application\n                  server. The following steps give an example of how to check users information in\n                  the application shell.</p>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"jon1665702865162__li_d11045e1_d11046e1_d11047e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Define an application shell for the Uniface Server, for example, <code class=\"ph codeph\">webasv</code>.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"jon1665702865162__li_d11048e1_d11049e1_d11050e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"jon1665702865162__p_d22583e1_d22584e1_d22585e1\">In the preRequest trigger of\n                  <code class=\"ph codeph\">webasv</code>, check the user name and the password, for example: </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">if($user !=\"correct-user\" | $password != \"password-for-the-correct-user\") \n return (-21)\nendif</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">correct-user</code>and the\n                     <code class=\"ph codeph\">password-for-the-correct-user</code>are only for the demonstration\n                  purpose.</p>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"jon1665702865162__li_d11051e1_d11052e1_d11053e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Compile the application shell and add it to a UAR.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"jon1665702865162__li_d11054e1_d11055e1_d11056e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Edit the assignment file of the Uniface Router to specify the new server application shell. For example:\n </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">; For Uniface WebApplication Server\nwasv = \"D:/Uniface/Uniface10/common/bin/userver.exe webasv.aps\" /dir=\"D:/Uniface/Uniface10/project\" /adm=\"D:/Uniface/Uniface10/uniface/adm\" /asn=wasv.asn</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"jon1665702865162__li_d11057e1_d11058e1_d11059e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"jon1665702865162__p_d22586e1_d22587e1_d22588e1\">Edit the assignment file of the Uniface Web\n               Application Server to use the new application shell. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">In <span class=\"ph filepath\">wasv.asn</span>, list the application shell higher in the\n                  [RESOURCES] section than <span class=\"ph filepath\">userver.aps</span>For example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[RESOURCES] \n c:/MyCompany/aps/webasv.aps\n c:/MyCompany/webapp.uar\n c:/MyCompany/webapp@usa.uar\n c:/MyCompany/aps/userver.aps</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jon1665702865162__p_d22589e1_d22590e1_d22591e1\">Classic deployment: In\n                     <span class=\"ph filepath\">wasv.asn</span>, redirect the <code class=\"ph codeph\">usys:userver.aps</code>to\n                  the location of the compiled application shell, for example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">usys:userver.aps usys:../project/aps/webasv.aps</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/noh1665702742459.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>AUTHORIZATION</a><p>Instructs the WRD that user authorization is required. If not specified, the web server determines whether, and what kind of, user authorization is performed.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528973\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528973\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Using Uniface Authentication Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 14, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Using Uniface Authentication To use Uniface’s authentication method: In the servlet specification, add the AUTHORIZATION parameter, for example, <servlet> <servlet-name> wrd … … <init-param> <param-name>AUTHORIZATION</param-name> <param-value>Realm</param-value> </init-param> </servlet> Copy If the Web server is Tomcat, the servlet specification is in web.xml . With this setting, a logon box is displayed for each first access of a server page by a particular user. The user name and password are available for the duration of the whole session. You can use $user and $password to access them. To validate the user name and password, you need to add ProcScript in the server page, or in the startup shell of the application server. The following steps give an example of how to check users information in the application shell. Define an application shell for the Uniface Server, for example, webasv . In the preRequest trigger of webasv , check the user name and the password, for example: if($user !=\"correct-user\" | $password != \"password-for-the-correct-user\") return (-21) endif Copy The correct-user and the password-for-the-correct-user are only for the demonstration purpose. Compile the application shell and add it to a UAR. Edit the assignment file of the Uniface Router to specify the new server application shell. For example: ; For Uniface WebApplication Server wasv = \"D:/Uniface/Uniface10/common/bin/userver.exe webasv.aps\" /dir=\"D:/Uniface/Uniface10/project\" /adm=\"D:/Uniface/Uniface10/uniface/adm\" /asn=wasv.asn Copy Edit the assignment file of the Uniface Web Application Server to use the new application shell. In wasv.asn , list the application shell higher in the [RESOURCES] section than userver.aps For example: [RESOURCES] c:/MyCompany/aps/webasv.aps c:/MyCompany/webapp.uar c:/MyCompany/webapp@usa.uar c:/MyCompany/aps/userver.aps Copy Classic deployment: In wasv.asn , redirect the usys:userver.aps to the location of the compiled application shell, for example: usys:userver.aps usys:../project/aps/webasv.aps Copy Related Links AUTHORIZATION Instructs the WRD that user authorization is required. If not specified, the web server determines whether, and what kind of, user authorization is performed. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}